	   <tr><td colspan=2>Aye, horses are sold in the Bazaar, you can go to www.eqatlas.com for maps.<br><br>But at your level, I would not purchase a horse.  They are very expensive, especially for the really good horses.  As a Paladin, you are better to begin earning your alternate advancement points until you get Holy Steed.  We Paladins get the innate ability to summon the ultimate of steeds, the Uber Horse, if you will.  You would be better to work toward this than to waste money on a horse you will not keep.<br><br>Greywen Ellsidell<br>30th Rank Paladin<br><br>&nbsp;<br>-Maintaining the Honor of Test</td></tr>
